cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with computational complexity theory, specifically second-order complexity theory, and its application to interval computation. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of functions and their representations, which suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) as possible sub-categories. The use of nested interval enclosures and dyadic rational approximation indicates cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the study of real number computation and optimization suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible sub-category.
